	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">MottZilla wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">If you're going to start enhancing the NES, another 6K of WorkRAM ($800-$1FFF) would be nice. DMA from CPU bus to PPU bus would be handy too. While we are at it, overclocking without altering audio generation would be very neat as well. Other useful things would be a built in PPU based IRQ, like MMC5's scanline counter functionally. Oh another 2K for 4 nametables total would be nice to include as well.</div>
<br />
<br />If you really wanted to, (with the exception of overclocking) couldn't you do most of this on a cart with an unmodified NES?

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


